{"info": {"author": "Ove Bepari", "author_email": "ovebepari@gmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["Environment :: Web Environment", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Topic :: Internet :: WWW/HTTP :: WSGI :: Application"], "description": "### web_share_ftp - A Simple Flask App to Share Files Over the Network\n\nThis is a simple flask app / cli tool that serves your current folder to share files from the host to the client browser or upload to host from a client browser.\n\nTo install on GNU/Linux, Debian / Ubuntu / Linux Mint:\n```bash\nsudo python3 -m pip install web_share_ftp\n```\n\nTo install on Windows:\n```bash\npython -m pip install web_share_ftp\n```\n\nTo start the server:\n```bash\nweb_share_ftp serve\n```\n\nTo access server from another device, find your local ip by checking `ifconfig` in GNU/Linux and `ipconfig` in windows.\n\nAnd of course I could use `http.server` for serving the files but I somewhat wanted to do it myself.\n\nHere's a web UI view of the flask app:\n\n![*web-share screenshot, check github if png not appears*](web_share_ftp/webshare-ftp.png)\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/ovebepari/webshare", "keywords": "", "license": "", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "web-share-ftp", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/web-share-ftp/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/web-share-ftp/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/ovebepari/webshare"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/web-share-ftp/1.0/", "requires_dist": ["flask", "click"], "requires_python": ">=3", "summary": "A Flask App to Share Files Within the Same Network", "version": "1.0", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h3>web_share_ftp - A Simple Flask App to Share Files Over the Network</h3>\n<p>This is a simple flask app / cli tool that serves your current folder to share files from the host to the client browser or upload to host from a client browser.</p>\n<p>To install on GNU/Linux, Debian / Ubuntu / Linux Mint:</p>\n<pre>sudo python3 -m pip install web_share_ftp\n</pre>\n<p>To install on Windows:</p>\n<pre>python -m pip install web_share_ftp\n</pre>\n<p>To start the server:</p>\n<pre>web_share_ftp serve\n</pre>\n<p>To access server from another device, find your local ip by checking <code>ifconfig</code> in GNU/Linux and <code>ipconfig</code> in windows.</p>\n<p>And of course I could use <code>http.server</code> for serving the files but I somewhat wanted to do it myself.</p>\n<p>Here's a web UI view of the flask app:</p>\n<p><img alt=\"web-share screenshot, check github if png not appears\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/90a4836b6e79f12c5460e518ecac7b4352aff288/7765625f73686172655f6674702f77656273686172652d6674702e706e67\"></p>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 4390738, "releases": {"0.10": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "c81d3c8684848fab3b716137cf6f52b2", "sha256": "ced31a466d36af62d5be2c858244ad80f0b4de9b3048b7500e3e8221490c6afb"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "web_share_ftp-0.10-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "c81d3c8684848fab3b716137cf6f52b2", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": ">=3", "size": 4732, "upload_time": "2018-10-18T15:12:24", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2018-10-18T15:12:24.676845Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/5f/d0/f27deb322207e7360bed1377bc5c8a9334d28ef33f4c227fce414e35d729/web_share_ftp-0.10-py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "7cead018310709a9f691e6c77cb4d664", "sha256": "933f4fcf8fe37ed1dd67371f6fcda5ee4e47ec9fc26519a584b1abc16af8595f"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "web_share_ftp-0.10.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "7cead018310709a9f691e6c77c